articles.title: About me:
articles.description:
I am an evolutionary biologist and social psychologist (Ph. D. from University of New South Wales, Sydney Australia). Currently a Data Analyst for the [Atlas of Living Australia](ala.org.au).

I am interested in understanding evolutionary and cultural underpinnings of human behaviour, in particular, sexist attitudes and behaviours. I published a few papers on this at one point.

I value scientific transparency and reproducibility. I try to practice this as much as I can.

Passionate about music. Love all genres. I play piano sometimes.
